PRETORIA - The Justice, Crime Prevention and Security (JCPS) cluster chaired by Minister Nosiviwe Mapisa-Nqakula will on Sunday brief the media on the implementation of the Cluster programme of action for the year, following the 2017 State of the Nation Address.Minister Mapisa-Nqakula will be supported by the Co-Chairperson Minister Nathi Nhleko and members of the Cluster.The briefing will also outline progress that has been made and future plans to achieve the National Development Plan Vision 2030.eNCA